ABDOMEN. S1 black with two small yellow spots latero-ventrally. S2 black, dorsally with a yellow spot, distal margin yellowish with another larger yellow marking covering half latero-ventrally. S1–2 broad, subsequently narrower toward tip from S3; S3 with a small yellow anteroventral spot; S3–5 with a small yellow ventral spot; S6–7 black, each with a subapical dorsal spot; S8 black with a short yellow lateroventral strip; S9 entirely black; S10 black with a yellowish marking on ventral side (
Fig. 26
).

SECONDARY GENITALIA.Anterior lamina broad basally, gradually narrowing apically and strongly curved posteriorly. Posterior hamule thin, as long as anterior lamina, slightly curved anteriorly at tip (
Fig. 32
).

